Horizon Scan Survey - Your Answers

Column

Dear Todd,

thank you for having participated in our survey! The red symbol in the figures on the right indicates your response.

For each topic we had asked you about your familiarity and the importance for the urban storm- and wastewater management sector. Topics with high importance and low familiarity were judged as “novel”.

Additionally we proposed for each topic a Vision 2030 (scenario). The second plot on the right shows how realistic and how desirable this vision was judged. In particular, undesirable but realistic scenarios can be identified.

The complete description of topics and visions (scenarios) can be found in the Supporting Information of the publication.

Publication

Blumensaat, F., Leitão, J.P., Ort, C., Rieckermann, J., Scheidegger, A., Vanrolleghem, P.A., Villez, K., 2019. How Urban Storm- and Wastewater Management Prepares for Emerging Opportunities and Threats: Digital Transformation, Ubiquitous Sensing, New Data Sources, and Beyond - A Horizon Scan. Environ. Sci. Technol. https://doi.org/10.1021/acs.est.8b06481
